<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RE1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d52fn1">Channel of transmission not indicated.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-22">22 October 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Most secret and personal from <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to President. Number 469.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Your 391. I am instructing <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> to back you up to the full but I do not think
                                Ankara would be possible; first, because of security, and secondly,
                                because there are the Taurus Mountains to cross.</item>
                        </list>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>4.</label>
                            <item>Whatever happens we have got to meet soon.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>